<div type="commentary">
   <!--The plate begins with two short marginal lines distinct from the body text. Fleet does not read the mangala symbol (in the top left corner, aligned with l1) and prints svasti (aligned with l2) at the beginning of l1. I believe śrī belongs with the mangala symbol in the marginal field. The third text line begins directly below svasti; the first two lines are indented to make space for the opener; the second line's indent is larger, because śrī encroaches on the space where this line could have been started. -->
<!-- Each extant plate has five lines. -->
</div>



